message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "Vision Language Models for Context-Aware Scene Understanding in Autonomous Systems"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Sampath Kumar"
    given-names: "Hariram"
    affiliation: "Eötvös Loránd University (ELTE), Faculty of Informatics — Erasmus Mundus Joint Master in Intelligent Field Robotic Systems (IFRoS)"
version: 1.0.0
date-released: 2026-07-20
repository-code: "https://github.com/ByteMastee/vlm-thesis"
abstract: >
  Implementation and benchmarking of three semantic mapping pipelines for
  indoor mobile robotics under ROS2 Humble: a classical YOLO26 baseline,
  a YOLO26 + Qwen2.5-VL 3B post-processing pipeline, and a fully
  open-vocabulary SAM2-small + Qwen2.5-VL 3B pipeline. All pipelines share
  a spatial estimation backbone (ray casting, pairwise triangulation, and
  DBSCAN clustering), evaluated across five Gazebo simulation environments
  and one real-world lab setting.
keywords:
  - robotics
  - semantic mapping
  - vision-language models
  - ROS2
  - autonomous systems
  - scene understanding
